From: stopless-java-gc <noreply@anthropic.com>
Subject: [PATCH 0046/N] jli_util.h: define JLI_Lseek for bsd target

`src/java.base/share/native/libjli/jli_util.h` defines `JLI_Lseek`
per-OS:

  #ifdef __linux__   -> lseek64
  #ifdef MACOSX      -> lseek
  #ifdef _AIX        -> lseek

No bsd case. parse_manifest.c calls `JLI_Lseek` and the cross-compile
errors out:
  error: call to undeclared function 'JLI_Lseek'

FreeBSD/CheriBSD `lseek(2)` is already 64-bit-clean (off_t is 64-bit
on LP64 BSD). Add `#ifdef _ALLBSD_SOURCE` -> `lseek`.

Refs: docs/05_zgc_cheri_collision_report.md (patch 0046)

--- a/src/java.base/share/native/libjli/jli_util.h
+++ b/src/java.base/share/native/libjli/jli_util.h
@@ -107,6 +107,9 @@
 #ifdef MACOSX
 #define JLI_Lseek                       lseek
 #endif
+#ifdef _ALLBSD_SOURCE
+#define JLI_Lseek                       lseek
+#endif
 #ifdef _AIX
 #define JLI_Lseek                       lseek
 #endif
